messages.message:
Looks like these changes are part of the redesigned build app. @Weiming Wu @CJ can  you clarify about this ?

cc: @Eric Han

I can repro this in the latest build in aihub-sandbox, seems to be coming from the recent navbar changes. This seems to be intentional in the redesigned navbar because the add button has shifted down?

This is a bug for the old converse navbar on prod  - it shouldn't hide the icon when `enable_build_latest` is false. Will create a fix.

This bug in prod navbar is unrelated to the My Conversation pinning change. It was caused by the updates in navbar design for the latest build - which converse is sharing. This didn't occur in build in prod because it uses the duplicated `build_23_07` directory with the old navbar code.

Created the fix here: https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/46937
